data.customers_say: Customers find the dog toy keeps their pets entertained for hours and is great for tug-of-war play. The rope quality receives positive feedback, with one customer noting its tight construction. The durability, size, and thickness receive mixed reviews - while some say it holds up longer than other toys and is good for large dogs, others find it doesn't last long and isn't suitable for really aggressive chewers. Value for money opinions are also mixed, with some finding it good value while others say it's not worth the price.

top_reviews.review_title: Durable. No, I mean REALLY durable.
top_reviews.review_comment: My dog is very tough on toys -- in my house, the "indestructible" label just means it will last for hours instead of minutes. But these ropes survive. I have a 60 lb pitbull and a 19-year old son, and they use these ropes in the most intense tug-of-war you can imagine; which includes the dog biting one end and my son hold the other and the two spinning so fast that all four of her feet are off the ground. This has been going on for months with the same rope. It's getting worn down and chewed up, but it still holds. If it ever completely falls apart, we're getting another. Definitely worth the cost.
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on March 23, 2025

top_reviews.review_comment: I have recently purchased these a second time. The original set survived over 3 years of rough play, my dog loves tug and also enjoys undoing the knots when they eventually come loose, I will reknot or I cut off the ends so my dog can't eat the string.
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2025

top_reviews.review_comment: My dog is the type of aggressive chewer that makes toy companies cringe. She can destroy a kong in under 48 hours, so when I say a toy is impressive, I mean it. These pictures are from after a month of constant play. We’ve had these toy ropes for about a month, and as you can see from the photos, my pup is still very much attached to these toys. She has chewed and chewed and chewed on them. The ropes started the fraying process a few days after we got them, but they have stubbornly held on despite endless doggy toy abuse. They’re about at the end of their lives now, but when I consider the cost to lifespan ratio, I am very pleased. I wasn’t expecting the length of the ropes though. The one in the picture is the one that comes looped in half. It has been the preferred one by my pup, but I think it’s because it is shorter than the other. The length of the other is so big compared to my girl that when she does the shake her head to kill thing, the knot on the other end whacks her in the back of the head. It’s humorous. I ended up tying that one a second time in the middle just to shorten it up. I suggest these toys for larger dogs than mine, based on the length. However, the width of the chew toy is about right for my 30 pound pup, which does pose a bit of a conundrum. Overall, if your pup is an aggressive chewer and chew-tug player, and you aren’t opposed to maybe tying an extra knot or two, this toy is great.
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on May 21, 2023

top_reviews.review_comment: My dogs absolutely love these rope toys! They’re big, colorful, and perfect for tug-of-war or just carrying around the house. They’ve held up better than most other rope toys I’ve bought, and they definitely keep my pups entertained. Not light and not too heavy. If you have a really strong chewer, they’ll eventually fray and come apart. Still, for the price and the amount of fun my dogs get out of them, I’d say they’re worth it!
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on September 3, 2025

top_reviews.review_comment: We have a Border Collie (M -2) and Australian shepherd (F - 1) who have a large yard for playing BUT, on the days it’s rainy or too hot for long outdoor play, these ropes come in very handy. The price point is perfect, especially compared to what we were spending at the “pet stores”. Admittedly, they go through them rather quickly so they are not the most durable rope there is but, for our purpose of occupying them for small bursts, they are perfect.
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on July 20, 2025

top_reviews.review_title: Durable and Engaging Rope Toys for Large Dogs
top_reviews.review_comment: I’ve been using the Feeko Heavy Duty Dog Rope Toys for my large breed dog, and they’ve exceeded my expectations. The set includes two sizable ropes—one 27 inches with four knots and another 20 inches with five knots—crafted from 100% natural cotton. These toys are perfect for tug-of-war and solo chewing sessions, keeping my dog entertained and active. The durable construction holds up well against aggressive chewing, and the cotton fibers help in maintaining dental hygiene by cleaning between teeth. While no toy is truly indestructible, these have proven to be more resilient than many others we’ve tried. Overall, a great investment for any large dog owner seeking durable and engaging toys.
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on May 25, 2025

top_reviews.review_comment: Our dogs really like playing tug-of-war with these ropes and except for the ends, the ropes are holding up; however, the frayed ends are not....The dogs are easily pulling strands out and I'm finding them in places on the floor/furniture. I now watch closely to determine if I should or should not allow them to continue to play with these.
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on October 2, 2025

top_reviews.review_comment: Not as big as I thought they'd be but are really sturdy and can handle a pitbulls rough housing. Wouldn't recommend leaving them with since the doggos will probably tear it up fast but great for tug of wars.
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2025

top_reviews_global.review_comment: Strong enough but the thread is ripping apart when my fury baby bites
top_reviews_global.review_date: Reviewed in the United Arab Emirates on April 4, 2023

top_reviews_global.review_comment: Mis perritas se entretienen mucho con ellas y a diferencia de otras cuerdas, estas son resistentes y no se deshilan fácilmente.
